  "level": 0,
  "ordinal": 0,
  "summary": "Main\nBy Jeffrey Landsberg\nGlobal crude steel production totaled 169.5 million tons in May. This is up month-on-month by 6.8 million tons (4%) but is 4.9 million tons (-3%) less than was reported last year for May's production. Global crude steel production has now contracted on a year-on-year basis for nine straight months.",
